history.text: Hi there
Hello!
Did you read the document about the movie?
I did.  The movie I suggest you watch is Toy Story.
That sounds like an entertaining movie!
Is that the older animated one?
Toy Story is an animated movie, and believe it or not, it came out in 1995.
Wow, that sounds really old. What kind of genre is it?
It is listed as a comedy/adventure.
It has scored well with audiences with a 100% score on rotten tomatoes

0% sounds bad
\
oh, nevermind. 100%
Is it marketed towards children?
It is marketed towards children, but some of the older toys are certainly nostalgic for adults
Oh, I see. So it's more of a family movie?
Is it rated pg?
Certainly a family movie.  It doesn't says if its PG, but I would guess it is.
Do you know anything about the plot?
When humans aren't around, the toys come to life and have their own lives.
Some of the voice actors include Tom Hanks and Tim Allen
Do the toys have a common goal? Is there a villian or are they just playing around?
The villain is the neighbor who likes to destroy toys and experiment with them.  When Tom Hanks character, Woody, gets stuck over there the other toys have to rescue him.
Do the toys ever get caught by humans?

Without spoiling it too much, they only get caught once and that's because it was part of their plan
.
That sounds amusing.
Does anything bad happen to them if they do get caught? Like, are there any negative effects? Or do they just avoid getting caught for fun?
Thats a good question.  It is unlikely anything happens to them if they get caught.  I think they avoid human contact to keep together.
Do all of the toys in the movie's universe come alive or is it only special ones?
They all come alive.  Mr. Potato head, rolling kids phone...you name it, it can communicate.
Tom Hanks plays a cowboy toy named Woody, the main character.
Who are the actors for the other toys?
Tim Allen, Don Rickles, and Jim Varney to name a few.

uid1response.feedback: The conversation went very smoothly and the other person provided a lot of entertaining information without spoiling the plot.
